756
00:34:57.513 --> 00:35:01.140
Yeah. well. I didn't think I would ever
see you meat-riding Homelander so hard.

757
00:35:01.141 --> 00:35:04.477
but... I guess we're both
just full of surprises. aren't we?

758
00:35:04.478 --> 00:35:07.814
- I take it you're not here to repent.
- No.

759
00:35:07.815 --> 00:35:10.526
I'm here to... to talk sense
into an old friend.

760
00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:12.819
You did that for me. do you remember?

761
00:35:12.820 --> 00:35:14.278
When. um... [chuckles]

762
00:35:14.279 --> 00:35:17.490
Alex and I were gonna get those matching
tattoos and you talked us out of it.

763
00:35:17.491 --> 00:35:19.784
A tramp stamp crucifix
is a bit of a mixed message.

764
00:35:19.785 --> 00:35:22.537
Especially on a shit-faced 15-year-old.

765
00:35:22.538 --> 00:35:26.666
But if memory serves.
you weren't so grateful at the time.

766
00:35:26.667 --> 00:35:29.043
Yeah. you know. it's hard to hear
that you're making a mistake

767
00:35:29.044 --> 00:35:31.505
you could regret for
the rest of your life.

768
00:35:33.131 --> 00:35:37.134
But... I...

769
00:35:37.135 --> 00:35:40.680
God. I wanted your approval
so badly back then.

770
00:35:40.681 --> 00:35:44.767
You know. you were like
a cool older brother that I never had.

771
00:35:44.768 --> 00:35:48.063
And you weren't cynical. like Ezekiel.

772
00:35:49.606 --> 00:35:53.402
You... you believed.

773
00:35:55.028 --> 00:35:56.529
I still do.

774
00:35:56.530 --> 00:35:58.240
In Homelander?

775
00:35:59.533 --> 00:36:00.784
Come on. Aaron.

776
00:36:01.869 --> 00:36:04.412
You know. I started preaching
when I was nine years old.

777
00:36:04.413 --> 00:36:06.915
in that moldy tent in Greenwood.

778
00:36:08.292 --> 00:36:09.917
And people would come and...

779
00:36:09.918 --> 00:36:13.045
beg me to pray for them.

780
00:36:13.046 --> 00:36:15.214
heal their illness.

781
00:36:15.215 --> 00:36:17.592
look after their children.

782
00:36:17.593 --> 00:36:19.219
get them a job.

783
00:36:19.887 --> 00:36:23.640
And I raised my hands in prayer
for each of them.

784
00:36:24.558 --> 00:36:26.393
Those prayers went unanswered.

785
00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:30.646
Nobody was listening.

786
00:36:30.647 --> 00:36:32.607
God checked out.

787
00:36:32.608 --> 00:36:35.651
Homelander is standing in front of us.

788
00:36:35.652 --> 00:36:37.695
He's not asking for blind faith.

789
00:36:37.696 --> 00:36:40.823
And when I talk...
when I talk. he listens.

790
00:36:40.824 --> 00:36:43.034
God is supposed to be selfless.

791
00:36:43.035 --> 00:36:45.244
Okay? Homelander...

792
00:36:45.245 --> 00:36:47.955
Homelander doesn't care about anyone
or anything outside of himself.

793
00:36:47.956 --> 00:36:52.168
Maybe imperfect. but he...
he brought this church up out of ruin.

794
00:36:52.169 --> 00:36:55.171
He fights back against the secular forces
corrupting this nation.

795
00:36:55.172 --> 00:36:57.423
He killed Firecracker.
and you're delusional if you think

796
00:36:57.424 --> 00:36:58.841
he won't turn on you.

797
00:36:58.842 --> 00:37:02.053
Firecracker was a nonbeliever.
she brought his wrath upon herself.

798
00:37:02.054 --> 00:37:06.308
I am not afraid to stand
before Homelander's judgment!

799
00:37:12.856 --> 00:37:15.692
But you didn't sneak in here
to argue about dogma. did you?

800
00:37:18.111 --> 00:37:20.238
Oh. Annie. I am sorry.

801
00:37:22.449 --> 00:37:24.076
I really did like you.

802
00:37:25.953 --> 00:37:27.746
[muted screaming]

803
00:37:28.956 --> 00:37:29.998
[Annie groans]

804
00:37:31.541 --> 00:37:33.001
[groaning]

805
00:37:37.464 --> 00:37:38.632
[muted screaming]

806
00:37:43.679 --> 00:37:44.845
[high-pitched ringing]

807
00:37:44.846 --> 00:37:46.181
[groaning]

808
00:37:47.849 --> 00:37:49.351
[Hughie] Stop.

809
00:37:51.144 --> 00:37:53.021
You know what this is?

810
00:37:53.647 --> 00:37:56.608
I open it. you're dead in 30 seconds.

811
00:38:01.363 --> 00:38:02.613
So is Annie.

812
00:38:02.614 --> 00:38:04.658
No.

813
00:38:06.118 --> 00:38:07.911
She already took the antidote.

814
00:38:10.205 --> 00:38:12.915
You didn't go to all this trouble
just to waste that on me.

815
00:38:12.916 --> 00:38:15.084
No...

816
00:38:15.085 --> 00:38:16.586
but I will.

817
00:38:19.464 --> 00:38:21.133
Unless you let her go.

818
00:38:30.809 --> 00:38:32.393
Don't be a stranger. Annie.

819
00:38:32.394 --> 00:38:34.438
Room for everyone in our flock.

820
00:38:41.778 --> 00:38:44.488
[newsman] <i>Authorities are calling it
the worst environmental disaster</i>

821
00:38:44.489 --> 00:38:45.906
<i>- in U.S. history.</i>
- [crying]

822
00:38:45.907 --> 00:38:50.119
<i>An estimated 2.5 million gallons
of crude oil have already spilled...</i>

823
00:38:50.120 --> 00:38:51.787
Plenty of fish in the sea. bro.

824
00:38:51.788 --> 00:38:53.998
[laughing]

825
00:38:53.999 --> 00:38:56.542
But most of them are fuckin' dead.

826
00:38:56.543 --> 00:38:59.295
<i>...Vought Petroleum promised
a thorough investigation...</i>

827
00:38:59.296 --> 00:39:01.756
You think a fish holocaust is funny. bro?

828
00:39:01.757 --> 00:39:05.051
Uh. yeah. Payback's a bitch. bitch.

829
00:39:05.052 --> 00:39:07.595
[panting]
What's that supposed to mean?

830
00:39:07.596 --> 00:39:11.265
It means I flew up to Alaska.
swam down to your dumb pipeline

831
00:39:11.266 --> 00:39:13.018
and punched a hole in it.

832
00:39:13.727 --> 00:39:15.269
It wasn't even that hard.

833
00:39:15.270 --> 00:39:17.146
That shit is really poorly built.

834
00:39:17.147 --> 00:39:20.608
What? Why?

835
00:39:20.609 --> 00:39:24.445
You killed Adam Bourke. so I killed
a bunch of porpoises or whatever.

836
00:39:24.446 --> 00:39:26.531
Now we're even steven.

837
00:39:28.283 --> 00:39:31.118
[muttering]

838
00:39:31.119 --> 00:39:33.287
I killed one f... I killed one dude!

839
00:39:33.288 --> 00:39:35.664
You killed 1.4 billion fish. motherfucker!

840
00:39:35.665 --> 00:39:39.418
One human being who was
a national treasure. asshole.

841
00:39:39.419 --> 00:39:41.587
Not just some stupid fish.

842
00:39:41.588 --> 00:39:44.423
[breathing heavily]

843
00:39:44.424 --> 00:39:46.301
They were my friends.

844
00:39:48.512 --> 00:39:50.763
Sucks to suck. dipshit.

845
00:39:50.764 --> 00:39:53.558
[soundboard voice] <i>Stop. loser.
bro-bro-bro!</i>

846
00:39:54.559 --> 00:39:57.103
[Black Noir] So let's record
this stupid fucking thing.

847
00:39:57.104 --> 00:39:59.606
[intense music playing]

848
00:40:05.362 --> 00:40:07.447
[grunting]

849
00:40:17.415 --> 00:40:18.833
[yells]

850
00:40:18.834 --> 00:40:21.168
[grunting]

851
00:40:21.169 --> 00:40:23.754
You were never my bro. bro.

852
00:40:23.755 --> 00:40:24.965
[grunting]

853
00:40:30.679 --> 00:40:32.681
[breathing heavily]

854
00:40:40.021 --> 00:40:41.523
No.

855
00:40:49.489 --> 00:40:50.991
[exhales] Oh. God.

856
00:40:58.248 --> 00:40:59.541
Oh. God.

857
00:41:02.127 --> 00:41:03.670
[door slams]

858
00:41:08.300 --> 00:41:11.969
Hey. Some kid shit on the floor
in the men's room. Again.

859
00:41:11.970 --> 00:41:14.472
[sighs] Terrific.

860
00:41:17.642 --> 00:41:19.310
[laser blasting]

861
00:41:19.311 --> 00:41:20.478
[body thuds]

862
00:41:26.985 --> 00:41:32.615
Bubelah. You might not remember.
but we actually met. back-back in the day.

863
00:41:32.616 --> 00:41:34.658
You must have been yay-high.
but you know what?

864
00:41:34.659 --> 00:41:37.912
I-I saw greatness in you. even then.

865
00:41:37.913 --> 00:41:39.705
I don't remember that. Chet.

866
00:41:39.706 --> 00:41:42.583
[scoffs] I did.

867
00:41:42.584 --> 00:41:44.919
- Um...
- Well.

868
00:41:44.920 --> 00:41:47.171
we needed to talk in private.

869
00:41:47.172 --> 00:41:48.881
Okay.

870
00:41:48.882 --> 00:41:54.053
I take it you saw the security footage
from the old folks' home.

871
00:41:54.054 --> 00:41:56.931
And you probably got
the very reasonable impression

872
00:41:56.932 --> 00:42:00.517
that I'm somehow working
with Butcher and them.

873
00:42:00.518 --> 00:42:02.895
Uh. but honestly?

874
00:42:02.896 --> 00:42:04.480
Fuck those guys.

875
00:42:04.481 --> 00:42:07.441
Fuck 'em. I'm on your--
I'm on Team You. big guy.

876
00:42:07.442 --> 00:42:11.528
And-and-and. I mean. I'll gladly
tell you any-anything you want to know.

877
00:42:11.529 --> 00:42:13.657
[tense music playing]

878
00:42:17.035 --> 00:42:18.036
Great.

879
00:42:19.663 --> 00:42:21.081
That's great.

880
00:42:25.001 --> 00:42:26.002
[lighter flicks]

881
00:42:28.255 --> 00:42:29.964
{\an8}- Tell me somethin'.
- Hmm?

882
00:42:29.965 --> 00:42:31.215
You got all this figured out.

883
00:42:31.216 --> 00:42:35.135
But you still end up trapped in a bunker
eating canned tuna and Chef Boyardee?

884
00:42:35.136 --> 00:42:36.637
Ooh. Crunchwraps. please.

885
00:42:36.638 --> 00:42:40.099
And. uh. solitude...

886
00:42:40.100 --> 00:42:42.434
is all I ever wanted.

887
00:42:42.435 --> 00:42:44.728
Since way before
Homelander knocked on my door.

888
00:42:44.729 --> 00:42:48.440
It's... gonna be magnificent.

889
00:42:48.441 --> 00:42:50.025
You're fuckin' crazier than I thought.

890
00:42:50.026 --> 00:42:51.402
And I thought you were fuckin' crazy.

891
00:42:51.403 --> 00:42:55.781
Sorry. are you not working day and night
to drop a genocidal virus?

892
00:42:55.782 --> 00:42:58.534
Yeah. but I ain't gotta enjoy it.

893
00:42:58.535 --> 00:43:01.954
- I just gotta do it.
- Don't pretend you're better than me.

894
00:43:01.955 --> 00:43:04.665
Enjoy it. don't enjoy it...

895
00:43:04.666 --> 00:43:06.584
it's still mass murder.

896
00:43:07.877 --> 00:43:09.838
Least I'm honest about it.

897
00:43:18.888 --> 00:43:22.392
[rumbling]

898
00:43:27.605 --> 00:43:29.316
- Right on cue.
- [whooshing]

899
00:43:36.448 --> 00:43:38.450
[dramatic music playing]

900
00:43:42.495 --> 00:43:45.497
Oi. Bombsight. glad you could pop in.

901
00:43:45.498 --> 00:43:47.374
Get the fuck away from her.

902
00:43:47.375 --> 00:43:49.710
Lookin' pretty spry
for a hundred years old.

903
00:43:49.711 --> 00:43:52.046
When you blow your load.
is it just a puff of dust?

904
00:43:52.047 --> 00:43:53.380
[Bombsight] You motherfuckers.

905
00:43:53.381 --> 00:43:55.591
I'm going to rip
every one of you to pieces.

906
00:43:55.592 --> 00:43:57.177
Try it.

907
00:43:59.054 --> 00:44:02.515
And you'll be wiping your better half's
better half off your fucking face.

908
00:44:06.019 --> 00:44:10.230
Now. how's about we just cool our jets

909
00:44:10.231 --> 00:44:15.195
and you and I have a little chin wag
like proper gentlemen.

910
00:44:22.118 --> 00:44:24.579
- [Homelander sighs]
- [The Legend] Okay. Um...

911
00:44:27.165 --> 00:44:28.624
- No one here.
- I grant you.

912
00:44:28.625 --> 00:44:30.167
it-it looks like that. yeah.

913
00:44:30.168 --> 00:44:33.837
But this-this is their hideout.
so I'm sure there's plenty of clues

914
00:44:33.838 --> 00:44:35.172
- all over here.
- Oh. come on.

915
00:44:35.173 --> 00:44:37.341
- Here you go.
- [sighs]

916
00:44:37.342 --> 00:44:39.051
Oh. no. well. this is nothing.

917
00:44:39.052 --> 00:44:41.470
but. you know. they have to
have left something behind.

918
00:44:41.471 --> 00:44:42.555
You know?

919
00:44:45.433 --> 00:44:46.476
Hmm.

920
00:44:49.062 --> 00:44:50.313
It's not nothing.

921
00:44:51.856 --> 00:44:53.107
It's a Taco Bell receipt.

922
00:44:53.108 --> 00:44:54.900
No. This is Sage!

923
00:44:54.901 --> 00:44:56.360
Taunting me.

924
00:44:56.361 --> 00:44:57.529
Okay.

925
00:45:00.573 --> 00:45:02.700
[Homelander laughing]

926
00:45:07.956 --> 00:45:10.959
This makes no sense.
This makes no sense.

927
00:45:12.210 --> 00:45:15.170
This makes no sense. [laughs]

928
00:45:15.171 --> 00:45:18.632
You... you said I would get the V1.

929
00:45:18.633 --> 00:45:21.009
You said I'd be a god.

930
00:45:21.010 --> 00:45:23.637
Did I do something wrong? Did I fail you?

931
00:45:23.638 --> 00:45:25.889
I did everything you asked me to.

932
00:45:25.890 --> 00:45:27.434
I gave my boy up.

933
00:45:28.518 --> 00:45:31.061
Please don't leave me here to just rot.

934
00:45:31.062 --> 00:45:35.233
Don't-- Just let me
become nothing. like him?

935
00:45:36.734 --> 00:45:38.277
[sighs]

936
00:45:38.278 --> 00:45:39.779
Please.

937
00:45:41.489 --> 00:45:44.324
Got to assume...

938
00:45:44.325 --> 00:45:48.787
the only reason
you're saying all this stuff is you're...

939
00:45:48.788 --> 00:45:51.791
you're not gonna let me
walk out of here alive. Are you?

940
00:45:53.126 --> 00:45:54.793
Yeah.

941
00:45:54.794 --> 00:45:56.129
Okay.

942
00:45:57.380 --> 00:45:58.756
Yeah.

943
00:46:01.676 --> 00:46:04.261
All right. look. kid.

944
00:46:04.262 --> 00:46:07.724
I-I-I've been around a long time. and I...

945
00:46:10.268 --> 00:46:12.352
This is just how it goes.

946
00:46:12.353 --> 00:46:15.606
You know. all those old Supes at the home.

947
00:46:15.607 --> 00:46:17.816
every one of them had their moment
in the sun.

948
00:46:17.817 --> 00:46:20.360
and they all thought
it was gonna go on forever.

949
00:46:20.361 --> 00:46:24.324
And every one of them got shoved out
at the end.

950
00:46:25.116 --> 00:46:28.244
They all got shoved out. All of them.

951
00:46:29.537 --> 00:46:31.498
And I know what I'm talking about.

952
00:46:33.458 --> 00:46:34.918
I did the shoving.

953
00:46:36.628 --> 00:46:38.045
I mean. look at Goldie.

954
00:46:38.046 --> 00:46:42.174
One minute she's on the set
of <i>Undercover Geisha</i>

955
00:46:42.175 --> 00:46:44.426
getting finger-popped by Lorenzo Lamas.

956
00:46:44.427 --> 00:46:47.054
the next she's shilling
for VoughtAlert necklaces

957
00:46:47.055 --> 00:46:49.807
and Activia poop-yogurt.

958
00:46:50.517 --> 00:46:52.434
Geisha sells VoughtAlert necklaces?

959
00:46:52.435 --> 00:46:54.562
Guess you don't
watch your own news channel?

960
00:46:55.855 --> 00:46:59.900
Point is. look. there comes a day
I got shoved out. too.

961
00:46:59.901 --> 00:47:02.694
Never saw it coming.
did not see that coming.

962
00:47:02.695 --> 00:47:04.363
And I fought it like hell.

963
00:47:04.364 --> 00:47:07.534
but in the end. bupkis.

964
00:47:09.327 --> 00:47:12.079
There's a natural order to things.

965
00:47:12.080 --> 00:47:15.958
and the more you fight the inevitable.

966
00:47:15.959 --> 00:47:20.255
the more the inevitable just
cunt-punts you.

967
00:47:24.050 --> 00:47:25.176
Yep.

968
00:47:30.431 --> 00:47:33.016
You're not scared of me.

969
00:47:33.017 --> 00:47:36.562
No. I'm not scared of you. I...

970
00:47:36.563 --> 00:47:38.022
I feel for you. kid.

971
00:47:38.940 --> 00:47:39.941
I do.

972
00:47:41.568 --> 00:47:43.319
You're a fuckin' whack-job.

973
00:47:44.404 --> 00:47:48.740
But. you know. that's talent. so...

974
00:47:48.741 --> 00:47:51.119
no surprise there.

975
00:47:54.664 --> 00:47:56.541
So. there you go.

976
00:47:57.792 --> 00:47:59.586
Do what you gotta do.

977
00:48:01.421 --> 00:48:02.463
[The Legend sighs]

978
00:48:06.092 --> 00:48:07.427
You can go.

979
00:48:10.471 --> 00:48:11.847
- I can go?
- Leave.

980
00:48:11.848 --> 00:48:13.223
No words. Just go.

981
00:48:13.224 --> 00:48:14.391
Now. Go.

982
00:48:14.392 --> 00:48:16.978
- Now!
- Yeah. yeah. Yeah. yeah.

983
00:48:26.613 --> 00:48:27.697
[phone clicks]

984
00:48:30.450 --> 00:48:34.244
[line ringing]

985
00:48:34.245 --> 00:48:35.787
[man] <i>How can I help you. sir?</i>

986
00:48:35.788 --> 00:48:38.750
I need the tracking coordinates
for a VoughtAlert necklace.

987
00:48:40.168 --> 00:48:42.170
[uneasy music playing]

988
00:48:46.382 --> 00:48:48.258
[Mother's Milk] Look.
all we're after is the V1.

989
00:48:48.259 --> 00:48:51.721
You hand that over
and we all go home happy.

990
00:48:55.475 --> 00:48:56.976
I can't.

991
00:48:57.894 --> 00:48:58.935
- Robbie...
- No.

992
00:48:58.936 --> 00:49:00.854
You'll change your mind.

993
00:49:00.855 --> 00:49:03.815
I've watched enough friends
get old and die to know.

994
00:49:03.816 --> 00:49:05.317
you'll change your mind.

995
00:49:05.318 --> 00:49:06.444
I'm sorry.

996
00:49:07.445 --> 00:49:08.446
But I won't.

997
00:49:11.074 --> 00:49:13.576
That doesn't mean we can't be together.

998
00:49:14.661 --> 00:49:18.081
We've wasted years already.

999
00:49:24.587 --> 00:49:28.382
If I gave it to you.
what would you do with it?

1000
00:49:28.383 --> 00:49:29.550
We will destroy it.

1001
00:49:30.802 --> 00:49:32.011
She is right.

1002
00:49:35.181 --> 00:49:36.641
It is a curse.

1003
00:49:40.603 --> 00:49:42.229
- No.
- [Butcher] Listen. mate.

1004
00:49:42.230 --> 00:49:45.816
You can sort things out
with the missus later.

1005
00:49:45.817 --> 00:49:48.360
but you ain't
leaving here with that shite.

1006
00:49:48.361 --> 00:49:50.320
You think I'm stupid enough
to bring it with me?

1007
00:49:50.321 --> 00:49:52.280
[Sage] You're exactly that stupid.

1008
00:49:52.281 --> 00:49:55.450
You thought Geisha's life was in danger.
